==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demoniac
<hw>De*mo"ni*ac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Demoniac
<hw>De*mo"ni*ac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
human being possessed by a demon or evil spirit; one whose faculties are
directly controlled by a demon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>demoniac</qex> in the gospel was sometimes cast into the
fire.</q> <rj><qau>Bates.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a sect of
Anabaptists who maintain that the demons or devils will finally be
saved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demoniacally</ent>⟦br⟧
